description:
**Problem**
\`crates/beads-rs/src/git/sync.rs\` imports \`crate::daemon::metrics\`, creating a reverse dependency from the git layer up into daemon. This layering violation blocks extracting git into \`beads-git\`.

**Design**
Introduce a trait seam so git sync can report metrics without knowing about the daemon.

\`\`\`rust
// git/observe.rs
pub trait SyncObserver: Send + Sync + 'static {
    fn on_fetch_start(&self) {}
    fn on_fetch_end(&self, elapsed_ms: u64) {}
    fn on_push_start(&self) {}
    fn on_push_end(&self, elapsed_ms: u64) {}
    fn on_merge_start(&self) {}
    fn on_merge_end(&self, beads_merged: usize) {}
}

pub struct NoopSyncObserver;
impl SyncObserver for NoopSyncObserver {}
\`\`\`

Wire into \`SyncProcess\` as \`Arc<dyn SyncObserver>\`. Daemon provides the concrete impl that calls existing metrics functions via \`git_worker.rs\`.

**Acceptance**
- [ ] \`SyncObserver\` trait defined in \`git/observe.rs\`
- [ ] \`SyncProcess\` accepts \`Arc<dyn SyncObserver>\`
- [ ] \`NoopSyncObserver\` available for non-daemon contexts
- [ ] Daemon provides concrete observer impl wired to existing metrics
- [ ] \`rg "crate::daemon" crates/beads-rs/src/git/\` returns zero matches
- [ ] \`cargo test\` passes
- [ ] Git sync behavior unchanged

**Files:** \`crates/beads-rs/src/git/sync.rs\`, \`crates/beads-rs/src/git/observe.rs\` (new), \`crates/beads-rs/src/git/mod.rs\`, \`crates/beads-rs/src/daemon/git_worker.rs\`
